<h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>
<h3>Are retro cakes really trending again?</h3>
<p>Yes — pastel piped buttercream cakes, sometimes called ''vintage'' or ''lambeth'' cakes, have been one of the most-searched cake styles on Pinterest and Instagram for the last two years and show no sign of slowing down.</p>
<h3>Do retro cakes cost more from a bakery?</h3>
<p>Usually yes. Piped shell and lambeth borders are hand-piped and time-consuming. Expect a 20–40% premium over a smooth-iced modern cake.</p>
<h3>Can I get a retro cake at short notice?</h3>
<p>For a hand-piped bakery cake, allow at least 5–7 days. For an AI mockup you can use to brief the baker, minutes.</p>
<h3>What''s the best flavour for a retro-look cake?</h3>
<p>Vanilla sponge with jam and buttercream, or a Victoria-style filling. The flavour and the visual language belong to the same era.</p>
<h3>Do retro cakes work for weddings?</h3>
<p>Increasingly, yes. Pastel piped wedding cakes are a strong 2025–2026 wedding trend, especially for intimate weddings under 60 guests.</p>

